betterquesting.name: Champion Of The Titans
betterquesting.desc:
If is no easy feat to conquer the Ars Magicka Titans.  For you valor in the face of danger, please accept this small token of gratitude.


§6Pro Tip§6:  This ring is similar to the Extra Utility Angel ring, however, the flight speed can be adjusted and the ring does not require any sort of power.

betterquesting.name: Journey To The Core
betterquesting.desc:
Difficulty: Extreme

Recommended Magic Level: 90

You will need to refer to the Arcane Compendium "Bosses" Tab for instructions on summoning this Titan.  Also visit am2.wika.com/wiki/Bosses for pictures of the summoning ritual.

§6Pro Tip:  This is quite possibly the hardest boss fight in this modpack... yes, even tougher than the Chaos Guardian Dragon if you have not prepared.  And by "prepared" I mean gone deep into the Ars Magicka spell schools, perfected some unique and powerful spells for protection and damage, increased your mana pool and mana regen extensively, and planned ahead.  But isn't this what you played this pack for?  This is Craft of the TITANS!

§aThe Ender Guardian has a lot of health, extremely high armor, health regeneration, flies insanely fast, teleports, and hits like a truck.  Good luck!

betterquesting.name: Fire Guardian
betterquesting.desc:
Difficulty: Extreme

Recommended Magic Level: 90

You will need to refer to the Arcane Compendium "Bosses" Tab for instructions on summoning this Titan.  Also visit am2.wika.com/wiki/Bosses for pictures of the summoning ritual.

betterquesting.name: Meteor Madness
betterquesting.desc:
A Tier 4 or higher Blood Magic Blood Altar allows you to perorm rituals.  The Mark Of The Falling Tower ritual will summon a meteor from the sky to slam into the ground.  When the smoke clears that meteor will be composed of helpful supplies, depending on the reagent you used to complete the ritual.  In addition to the usual Ore Meteors, there are 3 custom meteors you will want to summon.

§6- The Refined Storage Meteor is filled with everything you need to make a large comprehensive Storage System.  
-The Defense Meteor is filled with enough Top Teir base defense turrets and supplies to fend off even the most over buffed infernal mobs.  
-The Mystical Agriculture Metero is filled with mountains of Mystical Agriculture seeds, essence, Growth Accelerators, etc...

betterquesting.name: Advanced Generators
betterquesting.desc: Advanced Generators is a flexible multiblock power solution with options for RF/T production from late in the early game and onwards.  They are a bit expensive in this pack, but the materials are not rare.

betterquesting.name: GP, The Other, Other White Meat
betterquesting.desc: Grid Power is the power API for Extra Utility machines.  Extra Utility offers numerous fun ways to generate GP, but one of the best to set up early is the Water Mills.

betterquesting.name: How Would You Like Your Stone Cooked?
betterquesting.desc: Stoneburnt blocks are the foundation for most machines made in the Extra Utilities modpack.

betterquesting.name: To Make Power, You Must Spend Power
betterquesting.desc: There are bigger and more efficient forms of energy to come as you progress through the pack.  For now though, you will need to make some basic generators in order to create materials and start your processing.

betterquesting.name: Energy Emitter
betterquesting.desc:
The Energy Emitter is a block used to export energy out of your Advanced Generator.  You can hook Capacitors, Conduits, or other Energy Storage/Transfer devices up to the Energy Emitter to drain any RF currently in generator.

Reward Tip:  Now that you have a reliable source of early game power, you can begin using tools that require RF if you'd like.  §6The Energizer §fblock will recharge RF tools and weapons for you.

betterquesting.name: Gas Turbine Generator
betterquesting.desc:
The Gas Turbine Generator is the most efficient of the Advanced Generators.  It is able to run on countless different fuel types from dozens of mods.  The most efficient fuel types from this pack are the EnderIO Rocket Fuel and EnderIO Fire Water.

§6Tip: Although Fire Water produces "slightly" more rf/t in the gas generators... you may find it more convenient to simply use the Rocket Fuel, since you will already be mass producing it as Airship fuel.

betterquesting.name: Gas Turbine Controller
betterquesting.desc:
Each Gas Turbine has a few required components, and then a handful of optional components that increase speed, efficiency, output, etc...

§6Tip:  The Gas Turbine requires a Single Gas Turbine Controller.  This block provides the GUI for the player to control and monitor the machine.

§c§bReward Tip:  Power Cells are an inexpensive option for transferring rf/t over long distances and dimensions. You will need a Power Cell Card linking each cell together.

betterquesting.name: Finally, A Use for Aluminum Brass
betterquesting.desc:
Did you know that you can use the heat generated from Molten Metals to generate RF/t  So if you have an abundance of any particular Ore that you can't find a need for... use it for fuel.

§6Tip:  Simply Place the Tinkers Construct Stirling Generator on top of a tank filled with Molten Metal.  The metal will slowly fuel the generation of rf/t which can be cabled out of the generator into surrounding machines.

betterquesting.name: Gas Turbine
betterquesting.desc:
Each Gas Turbine requires, of course, Turbines.  You can add almost an unlimited amount of Turbines, but your fuel efficiency, output ratio, etc... will suffer as you surpass reasonable amounts.§6  For your current needs, a Gas Turbine Setup consisting of 3 Steel Turbines will provide you with plenty of RF/t for the late part of the early game.

§aReward Tip:  Advancing to the later stages of power production will require you to visit The Beneath.  This is a pitch black dimension full of danger... and rare ores.  These tossable glowballs should help light your way.  Also strongly consider completing the first few quests in the Ars Kickng Magicka questline to gain the Magelight spell.

betterquesting.name: The Real Reason
betterquesting.desc:
Make a plan of where your Steam Turbine will fit.  This is a large structure with a base that is 7x7, reaching 17 blocks high.  The good news, is that the reactor that you built earlier in the quest chain is a 7x7, so you could, if you wanted, place the Steam Turbine over top of your Actively Cooled Reactor. You will of course want to leave a two block space in between so you can access the Fuel Control Rods and run pipes.
§6Tip:  The great animations of the Steam Turbine allow you to see when it is spinning at the appropriate speed, at a glance.  I would recommend having 3 sides of the Steam Turbine made from Turbine Glass, and the back, top, sides, corners made of Turbine Housing.

betterquesting.name: Blade Runner
betterquesting.desc: In order to achieve optimum efficiency, your Reactor must have 10 rows of double depth Rotary Blades.  Meaning 4 blades attached to the Rotary Shaft, and 4 blades extending from those blades... stacked up 10 times.  Above this setup of blades, will be your Induction Coil... which is simply 36 Blocks of Ludicrite encircling the Rotary shaft up to the ceiling.

betterquesting.name: What Goes In, Must Come Out
betterquesting.desc:
The goal of your Actively Cooled Reactor and Steam Turbine set up is this:
§6-A water source sends massive quantities of water into your Actively Cooled Reactor so that it can be heated up.
§b-The Actively Cooled Reactor must send 2000mb/t of that hot Steam through it's Reactor Coolant Port, over to your Steam Turbine.  
§6-The Steam Turbine Accepts the 2000mb/t  through it's own Turbine Fluid Port set to import, converts the steam to kinetic energy, and sends the resulting water back to the Actively Cooled Reactor to be recycled.

betterquesting.name: The Ludicrous Cost Of Ludicrite
betterquesting.desc:
The induction coils are the most expensive portion of the Turbine.  It is 36 blocks of highly heat conductive blocks made of a substance called ludicrite.  To achieve the most power, the most efficiently, you will need to craft 36 of these.  They will form an encasement around the top 5 sections of your Rotor Shaft.

§6Tip:  Ludicrite blocks are available in the §9§bUncommon Titan Trades §5§6tab, if you don't feel inclined to craft them yourself.

betterquesting.name: Power Capacitor
betterquesting.desc:
Its time to assemble your Advanced Generator.  Your final piece is a Power Capacitor to increase the size of the internal buffer.  The great thing about Advanced Generators is that the multiblock can be formed any way you see fit, as long as all blocks from that network are touching a piece of the network.

Once the structure is set up, hook a fluid pipe the Fluid Input Valve and begin filing your tank with Rocket Fuel, you will begin to see the generator in action

betterquesting.name: The Finished Product
betterquesting.desc:
Once your Turbine is up and running, take careful notice of the tool tips that will guide you as you hover over the GUI options.  They will show you the optimal RPMs for your turbine.  It WILL take a half hour or so for your Turbine to spin up to the proper RPMs, but it should hover at the optimal point if you have built it as the quests described.  
§bIf you are unsure of exactly how the reactor pieces fit together, you can reference the wiki, or many youtube videos available for instruction.  I will link one in particular below.  

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FxcQvoD3TJ0&feature=youtu.be&t=872§6

ENJOY YOUR NEWFOUND POWER HOUSE!

betterquesting.name: Energy Emitter and Fluid Intake
betterquesting.desc:
You need a way to feed Gas to your machine for it to burn... this is where the §6Fluid Intake Valve §fcomes into play.  Hook pipes, or machines configured to output directly to the fluid intake and it will fill the internal buffer.

Your internal buffer is generally very small; Adding §6Fuel Tank §fblocks will drastically increase the amount of fuel the buffer can hold in reserve.  When the machine is NOT producing power because the Capacitors are full and no RF is being used... the fuel will sit in the tank indefinately.

§aReward Tip: §f Actually Additions allows you to transfer items, fluids, and energy over short distances using the magic of lasers.  Place on on the The Vat or fuel processor, and the other on the Fluid Intake Valve of of the Gas Turbine Generator.

betterquesting.name: Living Off The Grid
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: You Made it, Might As Well Use It
betterquesting.desc: Until you get a more robust RF/T system established, you will want to make good use of machines that run on alternative power options.  This crusher will assist you in processing ore from your mining trips.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: Water mills have the ability to generate up to 16 GP each... thats 4 GP per side.  The amount of GP each side produces is dependant on how far away from the source block of water it is.  The Water Mills will produce the most GP if each side of it is exactly one block away from the source block of water running past it.  Experiment with your set up to get the most GP possible.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Environmental Controller for Bosses
betterquesting.desc:
Although your airship is quite handy for many uses... you may find it tough to manuever during boss battles.  When you are about to summon a difficult boss, prepare the area with things to give you an advantage. 
§6 One of these would be the Environmental Controller.  This is a block that lets you tweak the atmosphere to allow for specific things to happen.  You can tell it to damage mobs within its range, give Regeneration to friendlies within its range, give creative flight to those within its range, and more.

betterquesting.name: Dont Get It Blown Up
betterquesting.desc: There are usually large explosions accompanying any large boss battle  Cover your Envronmental controller in a material like obsidian to prevent it from being damaged or knocked off line during a fight.

betterquesting.name: Regeneration Nation
betterquesting.desc: Keep in mind that each of these modules that you place into the environmental controller costs RF/T. Some are more expensive than others.

betterquesting.name: All Your Environment Are Belong To Me
betterquesting.desc: The Environmental Controller GUI has the option to designate what coordinates you want to cover with the specific buffs you have installed.  So if you want flight to cover the entire End Island while you fight the dragon, you will need to place the controller in the center of the island, then tell the Controller to cover (for example) Y60, which is the height of the island... and X75 which is a radius of 75 blocks around the controller.  This is just an example, you will need to do some testing to make sure the area is covered as you wish.  You will notice buff particles while you are protected by the controller.

betterquesting.name: The Darkness Calls
betterquesting.desc: There are a few new biomes in the overworld that have been inected by the Abyssal Plague.  You will want to find the Darklands Mountain and the Coralium Infested Swamp biomes.  Once you have located the swamp, crack open a few of those sweet sweet Coralium Ore blocks, and bring us back a few blocks.

betterquesting.name: **Disclaimer**
betterquesting.desc:
Abyssalcraft is a large mod full of in-depth rituals and processes that give the player a sense of accomplishment when completing the gauntlet of content.  In other words... some of the tasks needed to progress through Abyssalcraft can be tedious when combined in a modpack with other Magic Mods that also require a bit of grinding.  I felt that it didn't fit the pace or theme of this modpack to include each and every aspect of those tasks in the main quest line.

 For that reason, I made the decision to offer you an abbreviated path through Abyssalcraft using a quest chain that I feel still covers all of the key themes, while bridging over some of the grinding that would otherwise need to be done.

§6Long story short:  This quest chain, and its rewards drastically shorten the usual amount of tasking required to progress through Abyssalcraft. If you would still like to complete every aspect of the mod as it was intended by the Author i.e. Crystallizing, Altar Building, Necronomicon Empowering, etc...  I encourage you to do so using the in-game documentation and abbsalcraft wiki site.

betterquesting.name: Gateway Key
betterquesting.desc:
You will need to create two Coralium Pearls by placing any combination of 9 Coralium gems in between two rows of Stone.  See NEI for details.

§7§7§7§6Coralium Ore is most commonly found in the Overworld biomes Darkland Mountains and Ocean, and of course the Abyssalcraft Biomes.

betterquesting.name: When In Rome
betterquesting.desc:
Although some tools you may find in the overworld seem better, there are materials in the Abyssal Dimensions that only respond to the compounds found in Abyssal Tools.  Its wise to always keep a high tier Abyssal Pickaxe on you.

Pro Tip:  Have you picked up some pieces of Abyssalnite armor in Loot Bags, but have no need for them?  The Decrafting Table may be able to turn them into ingots, which you can use for tools.

betterquesting.name: And Into The Abyss We Go
betterquesting.desc:
Shift Right Click on the ground to open the portal to the Abyssal Wasteland.  You should be aware that this place is filled with undead creatures, dragons, and zombies.  You should find a good place where you can protect yourself from them.  Make sure your armor is enchanted, your weapons are repaired, your potions are restocked, and your Airship is fueled.

§6Things to take note of in here:

-Most of the enemies  Abysslcratf are undead.  This means of healing potion that restore health to you deals damage to te enmies.
 
§f-If you combined 8 9-clusters of Coralium Gems with 1 block of Abyssal Stone, you get a chunk of Coralium, which you can smelt for Refined Coralium Ingots, allowing you to either craft, or upgrade your Abyssalnite armor/tools to Refined Coralium armor/tools.

betterquesting.name: Powerstone Tracker Hacker
betterquesting.desc:
Surrounding an Ender Pearl with Coralium Gems you can create Powerstone Trackers.  These function just like Eyes Of Ender, but point the way to the Dreadlands Infused Powerstone where§6 you will summon the Dragon Titan known as "Asorah, The Fallen".  §f

Just like using Eye of Enders to locate Overworld Strongholds, the Powerstone Tracker will float in the direction of the nearest stronghold, then fall to the ground or dissappear.  The stronghold may be far away, so dont neglect to pick the Tracker's off the ground and reuse them.

betterquesting.name: Summoning The Beast
betterquesting.desc:
Once you begin seeing Abyssal Brick walls, you have found the stronghold.  Plan ahead on where you want to fight the Titan.  If you fight her out in the open, expect to be fending off a constant wave of mobs and Spectral Dragons during the fight.  

§aAnother option is to burrow down to almost Bedrock level, and create a large 20x20 clearing in the stone, leaving about 10 blocks of height in the room.  Performing your ritual here should summon the Dragon Titan into a confined area where you can fight without interruption.  You must set up the summoning ritual described in your Abyssal Wasteland version of the Necronomicon.  This involves placing 9 pieces of Abyssal Cobblestone into a "clock" formation as such:

§9 §6§d       O
    O      O
   
  O    O    O 

    O      O
        O 

§f(If that diagram is too horrible, consult the Rituals section of the Necronomicon)
Shift+Click the center piece of Abyssal Cobblestone to form the Altar.  Once the pillars have formed:

§6-You must place a Gold Ingot on the 12, 3, 6, and 9 oclock positions. 
-Place a Transmutation Gem at the 2oclock position.  
-A bucket of Liquid Coralium at the 4 oclock position
-An enchanting table at the 7 oclock position.  

§fOnce everything is in place, sweep the area for any mobs or Spectral Dragons, and get rid of them... or they will heal the Dragon during the fight.  Then Shift+Right click the center pillar of the altar with your Abyssal Wasteland Necronomicon one more time to summon the Titan.  Use potions, buff apples, and food as needed.

betterquesting.name: Packing For The Trip
betterquesting.desc:
You have a few tasks to plan ahead for while you are in the Abyssal Wastelands.  Or you  may find yourself having to trek back and forth quite a bit.

§6The Gold Ingots, Bucket, Enchant Table, and the Transmutation Gem will be used in the ritual to summon the Dragon Titan.

You are recieving an updated edition of the Necronomicon that will explain some of the Abyssal Wasteland specific details. 

The Ender Pearls will be crafted with Coralium Gems in order to track the Stronghold where the ritual will take place.

betterquesting.name: Defeat The Titan, Asorah The Fallen
betterquesting.desc:
For your bravery and Valor you have earned an Uncommon Titan Rune.  You can visit the Titan Rune Trade In tab now, or save it for later.  

The Asorah's, Gateway Key will point us towards our next Titan, but you may want to stop back at your base to restock.  It won't be an easy fight.

betterquesting.name: Do You Need a Hand With That?
betterquesting.desc:
Once you have found the Dreadlands Mountain Biome, clear the area of any Chagaroth Fists... their appearance means you are close to your destination.

§7§6Dig down to ground level 40 in the Mountain, and place the§a bottom piece §6of the Chagroth Altar exactly on Y40.  You will get a message if the altar is not at the right height.

betterquesting.name: Denizens of the Dark
betterquesting.desc: Familiarize yourself with the inhabitants of the Dreadlands.  As you hunt these creatures, look for a Dreadlands Mountain Biome.  Thats our next destination.

betterquesting.name: The Wall That Talks Back
betterquesting.desc:
Placing the top portion of the Altar onto the bottom, while at Y40, and clicking it will transfer you to the lair of Cha'Garoth.
§6This is likely to be the most challenging fight you have faced yet.  Cha'Garoth has over 2000 health, the room he is fought in is cramped, and there is a constant horde of Spawn of Cha'Garoth biting at your ankles.

§aTips:  If you have recieved or can make any of the Mystical Agriculture Buff Apples, they are helpful in keeping you alive.  Holy Hand Grenades work wonders to clear out the countless Spawn of Cha'Garoth that spawn throughout the fight.

betterquesting.name: The Final Abyssal Titan
betterquesting.desc: You receivd an egg to Spawn Sactoth, the final Titan of Abyssal Craft.  This is optional, as the dimenion for that boss has not been finished or releaseed ino the pack yet.  If you would like to summon and defeat him, there will be an Uncommon Titan Rune available to use in our Titan Rune trade area.  The egg is one time use... make sure you are ready.  The boss is fought in the same manner as Sactoth.

betterquesting.name: Where'd All The Cows Go?
betterquesting.desc:
The Titan Cloud City known as The Aether holds many valuable assets.  We will need to conquer the two Titan Entities of the domain to secure these delicassies.  Among the treasures are livestock with a rich and fatty meat.  The Aether Livestock (Flying Cows, Phygs, and Sheepuffs) drop§6 Cooking Fat§f that is a tasty substitute for Cooking Oil.   We should secure a stable of Aether Livestock, as this will make getting Cooking Oil for your Care Package preparations much easier in the end game.  
 
Prepare yourself, we must venture to the Sky Titan land known as §6The Aether.

betterquesting.name: I Believe You Can Fly
betterquesting.desc: If you weren't aware already, The Aether is a cloud city... lots of floating islands that can be anywhere from 20 to 60 blocks apart.  I would strongly recommend securing your first airship before venturing to the Aether to secure our livestock.  Your other option would be a hanglider, and some disposable blocks to get the height needed for the glide.  Either way, if you fall out of the Aether, you will land back down here on earth.... hopefully in water.

betterquesting.name: Dimensional Robbery
betterquesting.desc:
So heres the plan... we sneak in... we plunder their dungeons of any worthy goods... we grab a healthy variety of their livestock into Soul Vials... and make it back to earth before anyone's the wiser. Lets hope our plan goes that smoothly...

§6Enchanted Aether Grass works much like Fertalized Soil... but which one is faster? Aether Berries are the prime breeding reagent for Aether Livestock

betterquesting.name: While We're Here...
betterquesting.desc:
There are three dungeon types in The Aether.  Titans reside in two of them.  The Valkaryie Queen in the Silver Dungeon, and the Sun Spirit in the Gold Dungeon.  They are the only ones standing between you and returning to earth with your spoils.   Seek them out, and "ask their permission" to rob their lands.

§6Look for large more-spherical islands.  These are usually holding a golden dungeon at the very core.  There should be an entrance along the side of the sphere.  Find the Sun Spirit at the core of the sphere.  Right click to talk to him, then bring out the weapons when he is distracted.

betterquesting.name: All the Colors Of The Rainbow
betterquesting.desc:
It may be a bit more challenging to locate the variety of Moa that you will want to have for breeding.  Especially the very illusive Black Moa.  Venture out and see what colors you can find.  And while you are at it... clear the area of a few pesks.

§6Pro Tip:  Filter blocks only allow specific entities to pass through them.  A Filter Block for "Baby" animals may come in handy for your livestock farms.

betterquesting.name: Sheepuff?  I barely know her!
betterquesting.desc: Because Aether Animals are used to the free roaming flight environment beyond the clouds.  You may need to make certain accomodations them.  Possibly an enclosure with a roof on it?

betterquesting.name: Valkyrie Vengeance
betterquesting.desc: The Valkyrie race of the Aether has not allied with the Grimoire of Gaie Valkyries as of yet.  But that matters not.  They must be eliminated if your homeland is to have safe journey to this realm.  Travel to the dungeon where the Valkyrie Queen resides.  Dispatch ten of her Valkyrie underlings in order to anger her.  Then she will be willing to face you head on.

betterquesting.name: Mimicry Is the Best Form Of Flattery
betterquesting.desc:
The halls of the Aether dungeons are riddled with traps and treasure.  It is worth the risk however.  Break through the horde of traps to secure all that you desire.

§6Tip:  Did you know you can tame and breed Owls?  They will automatically attack any spiders in the area, and their eggs are highly sought after delicacies back in your homelands.  §a Breed Owls with Spider Eyes.

betterquesting.name: All Hail The Queen
betterquesting.desc: Right click on the Valkyrie queen after you have retrieved 10 Victory Medeals from her Underlings. This will provoke her to face you!

betterquesting.name: Better Than An Anvil, Half The Fat
betterquesting.desc: The Actually Additions Item Repairer does just that.  It restores the durability of a weapon at the cost of RF instead of materials.  So if you get your hands on an item made from materials that are tough to come by, this machine is the answer to all of your problems.

betterquesting.name: Infinite Lava Source
betterquesting.desc:
You can always use a bucket of lava, and with the Lava Factory, you will always have one available.

§6Tip:  The Lava Factory "multiblock" is created by having the Mob Factory block on the ground, the each of the 4 Casing blocks above and to the sides of the factory... creating a bowl like structure.  This machine will require RF to generate lava.  Pumps, including Extra Utility transfer pipes with Mining upgrades can be used to suck up the lava.

betterquesting.name: Craft At The Tip Of Your Fingers
betterquesting.desc: Keeping this in your inventory will allow you to open a crafting table anywhere at any time from your bags.

betterquesting.name: Double Venti Mocha Latte Frappe
betterquesting.desc: The Actually Additions Coffee Maker is very similar to the Minecraft Potion system.  There are unique combinations and effects that can be achieved.  Experiement and refer to the Actually Additons wiki for more information.
No Description

betterquesting.name: Plan For The Worst
betterquesting.desc:
You have a small window in the beginning to make your base safe.  After that, expect that very dangerous mobs will have increased AI, the ability to break down walls, and hordes to ambush your location relentlessly. There are two ways to deal with this.  You can fortify your base as best as possible, which can be very tough at the beginning of the game when you barely have enough resources to make a door.  OR, you can make a small battle tower, away from your base, where you can spend rough nights and blood moons.  A small 4x4x4 room made out of Reinforced Stone, with slots in each wall to swing your swords through.  Possibly add some hoppers or vacuum chests around the exterior to pick up mobs drops.

§6Pro Tip:  If you choose not to make a seperate Blood Moon Bunker, use these materials to solidify your base.  If you do choose the bunker, make it far enough away, that your base is not chunk loaded during the blood moon.  This offers additional security against property damage.

betterquesting.name: Choose Your Path Wisely
betterquesting.desc: Take a good look at the Titan Rune Trade Ins before planning your path of approach to the Care Packages.  You may decide it is wiser to spendy our Titan Runes on items that will increase your efficiency at producing more items... for example Growth Accelerators and Quarries.  It may prove quicker in the long run to improve your efficiency from the beginning.

betterquesting.name: Fluid, Fluid Storage
betterquesting.desc:
You will most likely need to develop a storage system for mass quantities of fluids as you  begin the Care Package dailies.  iTanks for great for this purpose, as they are modular, and grow as you stack more on top of each other.

ProTip:  The RFTools Builder block is a builder, quarry, relocator, and pump all in one.  For your purpose, you may need to to suck up Care Package fluids.

betterquesting.name: Whats In Store For You
betterquesting.desc:
If you are going to tackle the Care Package Dailies, you will need Object Submission Stations (OSS).  These are kiosks that can accept the care package contents, keeping track of your progress and triggering the completion when all of the contents have been submitted, just as it would if you had submitted them through the menu manually. You can submit both fluids and items through the OSS.

Tip:  You can have multiple OSS, each accepting contents for a different quest, or even sub-tasks of the same quest.

betterquesting.name: Welcome To The Jungle
betterquesting.desc:
Care Package Dailies can be considered "Side Quests" or "New Game Plus" content for this modpack.  None of these quests are expected or required to complete the main pack content. If you are planning to complete all of these, you will find that some of the quest tasks become downright ridiculous.  These are meant to give the pack rats, automation addicts, and sadistic achievement hunters a reward for their endeavors.  For those of us that may not have that level of engagement, it should be enough to just occassionally check quests against the items sitting in our storage system that we have in bulk.

§6TL;DR - You can either build big automated processes to complete these quests... or just occassionally cross reference your storage with these quests, and complete what you happen to be able to... leave what you can't.

When you get below 20% health it will teleport you to the location that you set. There is a cool-down shown by durability

betterquesting.name: Onyx, the Dark Diamond
betterquesting.desc:
Onyx, also called the Dark Diamond has been discovered in the Nether in limited quanities.  It is considered to be the strongest of the Molten metals, and will allow you to craft Tinkers Construct weapons that rival those of old.  You will definately want to take a look at the statistics of the Tinker's weapons vs. the Crafted Weapons to guage how you want your end-game arsenal to look.

§6Tip:  Some of the more difficult monsters in this pack are heavily shielded in armor.  Unfortunately brute force will not work well against Armor.  The Tinker's Construct Rapiers do Armor Piercing damage, so it is advised that you consider keeping at least one available for use in the end game.

betterquesting.name: The Brahemic Exchange
betterquesting.desc:
In an attempt to understand the mass hoarding of resources that Minecraft players long for, I once asked a man, 

§6"What can you do with 2,000,000 of something, that you can't do with 2,000?!"

§fIn his infinite wisdom he replied, 

§a"It's not about the doing... its about the having."


§fWell... challenge accepted.


I have no quest reward that would be sufficient for such a task.  I can simply say, if you complete this most audacious of feats....§c "You win."

betterquesting.name: Everlasting Abilities
betterquesting.desc:
Sometimes, you may want to have certain abilities, without having to carry around different potion bottles, wearing specific armor or using specific tools. This mod allows you to have persistent abilities, that stay on you after you die, and you don't have to carry around specific items.

You should have recieved an ability bottle when you first logged into this world.  If you have misplaced it, here is another.  This is your main interface for Abilities.

betterquesting.name: Respek Mah Athoritae
betterquesting.desc:
Each abiity till cost a specific amount of XP in order to equip it.  Some abilities are more expensive than others.  You must choose which abilities are most important to you, and make adjustments as necessary.

Some abilities are so impactful that you will want to swap them in or out frequently.  Fighting a tough boss with high armor?  Use the Poison and Wither totems to drain it's health whenever you are within range, and the Weakness Totem to make it's attacks more manageable.

betterquesting.name: Natural Absorbtion
betterquesting.desc:
In order to combat the countless enemies in your path, scientist back home have devised a process in which you can gain an energy shield to absorb incoming damage.  You must apply the knowledge you gain in each Instruction Manual titled "Book Of Absorbtion" in order to apply the shield.  Oddly enough you can craft these books yourself... because logic.

§6Tip: The Common Titan Runes required to craft the book can be found in Dungeon Chests throughout the world.  They can also be Molecularly Transformed from Copper Blocks using the Molecular Transformer from Industrial Craft 2.

betterquesting.name: Theres Always A Cost
betterquesting.desc: The ability to absorb incoming damage is such a powerful function, that it can not be delegated lightly.  In order to ensure you can handle such responsibility, each time you apply a book, it will cost 150 Experience levels.  This shouldn't be a problem for a hero of your caliber. Surely your Mob Farms and/or Mystical Agriculture plants can secure plenty of XP for you.

betterquesting.name: What a Creep
betterquesting.desc:
Mystical Agriculture is a great way to grow resources, including mob drops.  You will need a hefty amount of Gunpowder to make things like Rocket Fuel in this pack, so lets start with Creeper seeds.

§6Tip:  Slaying mobs with the Soulium Dagger has a chance to make them drop their mob "chunk" which is used in the creation of seeds for that mob type.  You are in luck, as the Soulium Dagger provided in the above quest has a little extra punch to it.

betterquesting.name: They Even Have Armor
betterquesting.desc: Msytical Agriculture Armor is very strong, and was previously one of the go to sets for early game creative flight.  Unfortunately, the weather in this region causes the purity of the seeds to suffer slightly enough that the armor no longer has the ability for flight.  All of the other armor benefits are still applicable, and the armor is comparable to the armor plus high tier options.

betterquesting.name: Withe Or Not
betterquesting.desc: Using Enderman seeds, it is possile create a safe-room for your Wither Killingfarm

betterquesting.name: Mekfarming For Meat
betterquesting.desc:
Mekfarm is a compact mod thats based solely around farm automation.  It runs on Tesla, which you will not have early game access to until you've got the MekFarm running for a bit, and can supply animals to the§6 Animal Gym. §f You can push forward and create Tesla power via the Advanced Generators or Extreme Reactors mods. 
§a For now though, we will assume you would like to get your Mekfarm set up as early as possible, and provide you with a packaged animals  to get started.  Keep in mind though, if you run through these packages before setting up your §6Animal Gym§f, you will need to push forward to other later game means of Tesla generation in order to run your Mekfarm.

betterquesting.name: The Butcher's Bakery
betterquesting.desc:
The Refridgerators are the main storage space of the CFB Kitchen.  They can be stacked two high, and dyed if desired.  Any food or ingredients inside of ANY of the storage units touching the Kitchen (including Refridgerators, Cabinets, Tool Racks, etc...) will be networked together, and taken into consideration when recipes are suggested.

§6Tip:  Your operation can be as large as you want.  It's not uncommon for CFB Kitchens to have a dozen Refridgerator units hidden under the maain kitchen, storing the massive quantities of food items they are using.  As long as they are touching at least one item from the main kitchen, they will all be within the network.  You can even control the importing and exporting of food in the refridgerators with Refined Storage busses.

betterquesting.name: All Animals Were Harmed In The Filming...
betterquesting.desc:
The Animal farm is a multi-functional machine.  
-given some shears it will shear sheeps
-given some animal packages it will package the animals for transport
-given some buckets it will milk cows
-given some bowls it will get soup from mooshrooms
-given some wheat, seeds or carrots it will try to feed animals 
§6It also accepts a range of filter items:
§fUsing a baby filter w/ animal packages, it will only package baby animals
Using an adult filter w/ animal packages, it will only package adult animals

betterquesting.name: Butcher?!  I barely know her!
betterquesting.desc:
The Mekfarm Electric Butcher block is used to slaughter animals.  Once given a sword it will try to kill the animals in its area of operation.  Using a baby filter will make it only hurt baby animals (but why?).  Using an adult filter will make it only hurt adult animals.

§6Tip: As all Mekfarm machines it has a base range of 7x7 located at the back of the machine (opposite to the side with the pretty cow face)

betterquesting.name: Gordon Ramstein Would Be Proud
betterquesting.desc: The Cooking Table is like your CFB Book in Block Form.  Whenever you want to view what meals can be prepared open the Cooking Table GUI.  You can select the meals from a list and the ingredients will automatically be used from your storage, and presented to you.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc:
The Animal Gym is a "Tesla Generator" of sorts.  If you place healthy packaged animals into the Gym GUI, they will spin their little hamster wheels to create Tesla Power.  Once the animals have become exhausted, the packages will be refunded, containing the exhausted animals.  They will need to be released, healed, and then repackaged if you want to use them again.

§6Tip: This is obviously going to be eating into your profits, as you will be using animals to generate energy instead of butchering them for their drops.  So you will want to escalate to at least a small amount of fueled Tesla generation soon. §a Also keep in mind that you can recharge Tesla powered Tools/Armor by placing them into the Animal Gym as well.

betterquesting.name: Meteor For Meat
betterquesting.desc:
Once you have reached the Tier 4 Blood Altar in Blood Magic, you will have access to summon the Refined Storage Meteor.  That will open up a world of automation for your Cooking For Blockheads kitchen. 

§6Tip:  Due to the sheer volume of farm goods and resources, it would be advised to have a completely seperaate RS network for your Agriculture.  This will simplify the importing and exporting of all of your farm goods.

betterquesting.name: Catch and Release Program
betterquesting.desc:
The Animal Releaser does exactly that... it "opens" animal packages that are piped into it, and releases them into a 7x7 area behind it.  For your purpose, this will take the baby animal packages from your Animal Farm machine in the Breeding Pen, and open them into the Growth Pen.  When the babies grow up, they will immediately be slaughtered by the butcher.

§6Tip:  You may ask, "Why not keep all the animals in one pen."  Well, because the butcher would slaughter ALL of your adults, before they got a chance to breed.  Keeping a seperate pen for breeding, allows you to control your production.  Not making enough meat?  Add more breeder pairs.

betterquesting.name: Frying Pan Into The Fire
betterquesting.desc: Many items you make will need to have some of the ingredients cooked.  The oven will automatically queue and cook the items you order.  Make sure to keep both cooked and uncooked foods in your storage to see the full list of available recipes, as some will require only one or the other.

betterquesting.name: Hells Kitchen
betterquesting.desc:
Any good farm needs a place to store their goods.  Constructing a "kitchen" will provide you with food storage, water source, cooking tools, and more at your fingertips.   Clicking on the Cooking Table of your Kitchen will provide you a list of all food items you can craft with the items currently in your inventory, including the storage blocks attached to the kitchen (Refridgerators, cabinets, and chests attached to the kitchen will be included.  Talk about convenient!

§6Tip:  Here are some decorative blocks to put together a kitchen of your choice.  Leave plenty of space!

betterquesting.name: Preventing Problems
betterquesting.desc:
One small problem with automating the breeding of livestock, is that it takes a lot longer for a baby to grow up, than it does for adults to have more babies.  Meaning, you will slowly have more and more babies sitting in the Growth Pen waiting to grow.  At some point this could reach really high numbers, eventually causing lag and TPS issues.  
§6To avoid this, place an Entity Detector in the floor of the Growth Pen, make sure it is set to cover just the size of the Growth Pen, and tell it to send out a redstone signal when the number of Animals in it's range exceeds 20 (or whatever number you feel safe with). Tie that redstone signal to the Animal Farm machines that are feeding the animals over in the growth pen.  Basically, this will tell the Animal Farms to stop breeding animals whenever the number of animals waiting to grow up, exceeds 20.

betterquesting.name: Here's My Counter Offer
betterquesting.desc: Counters are similar to refridgerators in that they have storage space which is connected to the food network for recipes.

betterquesting.name: I Guess This IS a Kitchen Sink Pack
betterquesting.desc: The sink is an incredible source of infinite water.  Incredible, because it is powerful enough to provide full water flow to an Extreme Reactor (as you will see later).  For now though, lets just worry about providing water for recipes that need it.

betterquesting.name: Put That Vat To Use!
betterquesting.desc:
Unlike Most modpacks where you B-line for Angel Wings, the Titans have ensured things won't be that easy here.  But don't fret, we have supplied you with flight options as you progress.  Vies Airships come in 3 Varieties. There is rumored to be a forth, slightly faster experimental Airship available, but Scientists back home will need some care packages to fund their research.   §6Rocket Fuel is a key fluid for both your airship, and your Advanced Generators.  You will want to make some hefty quantities in order to never be short on supply.  

§aTip:  JEI is glitched on the viesoline recipes, and shows an outdated recipe using redstone and coal.  The new recipe is the one using rocket fuel, and gives 4 times more output.

betterquesting.name: Pass The Gas
betterquesting.desc:
Now that you have a few pieces of Viesoline Airship Fuel, lets get started on your first Airship.  I know, she isn't much to look at right now... but at least you get to pick the color, and the next version is sure to be a more modern model.

§6Tip: Due to an error in JEI an outdated recipe for Viesoline shows up.  The correct recipe is the Rocket Fuel recipe that has a 4 pellet ouput.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Its Getting Electrifying Now!
betterquesting.desc:
Ok, so its time to step up to the big boy.  The end-game power generation. The Good stuff.  The Extreme Reactor Turbine is such a beast, that it uses another Reactor just to feed it steam. It's not cheap, but it's well worth the exponential increase in RF/T it will generate.

§6Tip:  In order to make the most efficient, yet biggest, Steam Turbine, we will first need to prepare our old Passively Cooled Reactor for the change.  Make sure that all of your capacitor banks are full on power... since your reactor may be down for a short while.

betterquesting.name: Measure Twice, Cut Once
betterquesting.desc:
To avoid having to do large renovations for your end game power generation, consider the layout of your Reactors and where the future turbines will go.  As mentioned, the appropriate size of the Reactor to power a fully efficient Turbine is 7x7x5.  In addition, the size of the future Steam Turbine will be an EXTRA 7x7x17.  Since both bases are 7x7, you could place one over the other (with a few blocks of crawl space in between), for an epic looking TOWER OF POWER.  But the choice is yours. §6 The only absolute requirement for the placement of your Reactor and for your Turbine, is that you can send Steam and Water back and forthe between the two structures.

§aTip: Also consider how much power you would like to produce.  Is 100k rf/t reasonable for your needs?  Or would you like to make additional space for more reactors, advanced, generators, etc...

betterquesting.name: Mobs Drop It Like Its Hot
betterquesting.desc: There is a group back home that would love to get their hands on this care package.

betterquesting.name: Time To Upgrade Ya
betterquesting.desc:
As usual, we would like to better prepare you for the elevated level of difficulty present in this modpack.  Deposit the Sentient Sword you crafted, and I shall enchant it for you.

§6Tip: §fThe Sentient Sword may seem week at first... but it gains damage as you collect Demonic Will into your Tartaric Gem.

betterquesting.name: Robin Hood If He Could
betterquesting.desc: Bows are strong in this pack.  Not only can they apply viscous status effects, but they keep you far out of harm's way.  The strongest arrows in the pack, the Ender Dragon Arrows apply§6 Wither 4§f to the target. More often than not, you won't need more than 1 shot.  Familiarize yourself with the recipe... you may be using it a good amount.

betterquesting.name: Tesla Tie In
betterquesting.desc: There are a small number of items in this pack that are run from Tesla power. Tesla is an energy source similar to RF, GP, and EU.  Hooking Tesla Power to your Mekfarm will allow you to stop running the farm on Animal Labor, and free up those livestock to produce more drops for you.

betterquesting.name: IC2 Of You
betterquesting.desc:
Industrial Craft 2 is an all inclusive mod that offers everything from Ore Duplication to Nuclear Power.  Advanced Solar Panels is an IC2 addon that incorporates versatile Solar Panel energy for EU production.  IC2 will be a big part of your Care Package production, and other end game priorities. 

§6§9§cKey IC2 Goals:
§6--Mass Fabricator - §aThe Primary Source for Iridium, an important ingredient in Nuclear and Solar energy production.
§6--Recycler Station - §aTakes random materials and turns them into Scrap which speeds up the Mass Fabrication process.
§6--Molecular Transformer -  §aPossibly the most powerful machine in the pack.  It has the ability to one item into another at the cost of EU.  Turn Copper into Titan Runes, turn Gold into Sunnarium, turn Irom into Iridium, etc...  A setup containing one ore more Molecular Transformers will be crucial to your end game success.

betterquesting.name: You Have To Spend Power, To Make Power
betterquesting.desc:
In order to make some of the machines necessary for processing of IC2 (and some other mod items) you will need to craft some temporary means of power generation.  Don't worry though, the output on these generators have been tweaked slightly to allow them to be less of a burden than they normall would be.

§6Tip:  Geothermal Generators create and transfer EU at twice the rate of regular Generators.  Transfer rate of EU is much more important in IC2 than in other mods.

betterquesting.name: Formal Metal Forming
betterquesting.desc: Metal formers are a great way to quickly produce plates, cans, and casings.  They can also be automated.

betterquesting.name: I Can Can With The Best Of Them
betterquesting.desc: You will find the fluid/solid canning machine is a very convenient way to make "buckets" of fluid that can stack.  It is also a key process in the creation of IC2 Coolant, which you will revisit as part of your Care Package quests.

betterquesting.name: First The Canner, Now The Scanner
betterquesting.desc: In order to decipher the proper combination of UU Matter required to duplicate an item, the item must first be scanned.  This process requires the IC2 Scanner.  Once the Scanner has processed an item, the pattern can be stored on a Memory Crystal, and place in Pattern Storage to be accessed by the Replicator when necessary.

betterquesting.name: Compressing The Right Buttons
betterquesting.desc:
The compressor does just what it sounds like... it condenses a small stack of items, into one solid unit.  This includes plates, compounds, and eve Coal!  Ever wonder what happens when you compress coal enough?

§6Tip:  Overclocker upgrades can drastically increase the speed of IC2 machines.  With enough of them, operations complete in a blink of an eye.  But be careful, the EU consumption goes up a LOT as you add upgrades.

betterquesting.name: IC2 Is Going Green?
betterquesting.desc:
The Recycler is a machine that accepts common items, recycles them with a chance to produce scrap.  Nine Scrap can be combined to make a scrap box, which you can open for a studpidly useless item.  You can also place the scrap or scrap box into a Mass Fabricator.  This is extremely important, and we will discuss more on why that is when you craft the Fabricator.  For now, expect that processing scrap is an important part of end game efficiency.

§6Tip:  I have good news and bad news.  The bad news is: You can not just feed cobblestone into the Recyclers like you did in previous packs.  The Recycling plant has blacklisted it. The good news is:  The Recyclers still take nearly all other types of material. AND! New ways to produce scrap have been developed, so you should not see a change in production.  View your Clash Of The Titans tip guide for more information.

betterquesting.name: Mass Fabulous Fabricator
betterquesting.desc: UU Matter is a dense syrup of creativity.  Scanning certain rare resourse, you can then reconstruct them out of UU Matter.  This is one of very few ways to gain more of certain resources that have long since dissappeared from the world, like Iridium. In order to form a drop off UU Matter, the Mass Fabricator must focus extreme amounts of energy into it's core.  This can be quite time and Energy intensive.  However, adding random pieces of matter via Scrap or Scrapboxes, you can greatly speed up this process.

betterquesting.name: Not The Blade Runner Replicants
betterquesting.desc: The Replicator takes patterns from the Pattern Storage (situated next to it) and replicates the item on the pattern using UU Matter.  UU Matter is not cheap, so you want to make sure this process is reserved for the rarest of materials.

betterquesting.name: Ready To Rock?
betterquesting.desc: So you have secured the necessary materials needed to move forward?  The next tier is the Advanced Solar Panel.  A slightly beefier version of the base solar panel.  Don't worry, this is the last 60x Solar panel part of this quest line.

betterquesting.name: You Can Grow WHAT?
betterquesting.desc: You are about to open the doorway for a level of automation only dreamed of back in your homeland.  This land is ripe for growing crops of all sorts... even Ore crops.

betterquesting.name: Inferium By Name, Inferium By Reputation
betterquesting.desc:
Inferium seeds and Inferium Essence are just the base level of component for Mystical Agriculture.  You will need literally hundreds of thousands of these if you plan on completing everything in this pack to its fullest.
§6The Inferium Seeds come in Tiers, each tier gives you a higher output of Inferium Essence.  When you get a decent stock of one tier, begin converting the seeds into the next tier up.  Your growth accelerators are limited, so you can't afford to waste them on lower tier seeds.

betterquesting.name: Compacting And Storage
betterquesting.desc: You have many options when it comes to organizing your Mystical Essence and drops.  If you have already achieved the Tier 4 Blood Altar and called down your Refined Storage system, you can set up autocrafting to ensure you always have what you need in stock.  Assuming you have not done this yet, a set up of crafters is an easy way to convery your essence into resources automatically.

betterquesting.name: RF, Never Leave Home With Out It
betterquesting.desc:
The wirelss charge will automatically charge any RF based items within a 64 block radius.  No more worrying that you forgot to charge your magnet before you left home.

§6Reward Tip: The Handheld Filler is an item added by Actually Additions. It is used to fill an area full of a specific block. Shift right-clicking a block will pick it as the block to be used in the filling. Right-clicking the first block, holding, and releasing on the second block will start the filling process (the first two corner blocks of the final structure must be placed). This formation can be in a flat plane or a cuboid.

betterquesting.name: Do You Mind If I Bind?
betterquesting.desc: You will find that the Soul Binder is a great tool for bending the life will of entities that you come across.  From harnessing the instincts of a zombie in a controller... or binding souls to a broken spawner.

betterquesting.name: Whether The Wither Will Or Not
betterquesting.desc:
One of the problems with mob farms, is that everything seems to explode.  This can cause a problem when trying to run pipes or hoppers into an area to pick up mob drops... sometimes they end up broken and destroyed. 
     The§6 Dark Utilities Ender Hopper §fhelps eliminate that problem by being able to teleport any drops within a 7 block radius through walls/blocks.  So you can hide your Ender Hopper behind blast/wither proof walls, and it will teleport the mob drops directly into the chest it sits on.

§aReward Tip:  Lapis Lamps from Random Things give off a light level of 15, but DO NOT interfere with the ability for mobs to spawn.  Perfect for keepin an eye on your mob farms.

betterquesting.name: A New Level Of Weaponry
betterquesting.desc:
You will notice, that as you pick up and craft weapons through the world, they are rated for quality.  This quality ranges from§9 "Rare",§d "Ultra Rare",§6 'Legendary",§c and "Archaic".§f The quality not only increases the durability and damage, but it also allows you more options for upgrading the weapons.

§fBy harnessing the Titan energy that taints the experience you pick up from mob kills, you can upgrade the power of your weapons.  Using a particular weapon in battle will eventually level it up.   By pressing the "L"key (by default), you will pull up the "Levels" mod UI.  This UI will allow you to spend the points you have accrued on POWERFUL weapon traits.  Elemental damage, Chain effects, etc... These upgrades are crucial for turning you into a force to be reckoned with.  Do not forget to apply your points each time you see the notification that one has levelled up.

betterquesting.name: Everything Has a Purpose
betterquesting.desc:
In most modpacks, there is a lot of stuff that just gets thrown away because it has no use.  We can't afford such luxuries here in Craft Of The Titans. We need all of the resources we can get.  Usually, damaged armor and weapon drops from your Mob Farms would just get filtered into a trashcan.  Our scientists back home have devised a way to put them to great use.  

§6All Vanilla Armor and Weapon drops, regardless of damage level, can be converted into scrapboxxes, simply by placing them into the crafting table.  §fSince there are no cobblestone generators in this pack, this is a key way to provide a steady stream of scrap to your Mass Fabricators.  You will most likely want to set up an automatic system, that retrieves the drops from the mob farm, crafts them into scrap, and sends it to your mass fabricator.

betterquesting.name: Lucky Block Buster
betterquesting.desc:
This Hazmat suit is designed to offer the max protection agains the woes of the Irish Lucky block.  It offers protection against Dynamite, Lava, Falling, and Suffocation/Drowning.  It may not save your life in all situations, but it's the best option you have.

§6These suits have very low durability.  So although they are great protection, they will probably leave you naked if you attempt to use them for normal combat.  These are meant as a disposable, one-time gift from your loving subscriber, to protect you from those less scrupulous viewers.

betterquesting.name: Somebunny Loves You
betterquesting.desc: For the subscriber that would prefer to be a longer lasting part of your gameplay.  These are the Rare Aerbunnies often found in the Aether.  These lovely creatures need a place to call home, and your subscriber just sponsored one.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Follow or Subscriber Options
betterquesting.desc:
These repeatable quests were set up so that your streamers have a choice.  Good or Evil.  They can opt to spend their Sub Gift on

§6-A 1-ish time use HazMat suit that helps protect you from the next Lucky Block that will come your way.
§b-An Aerbunny named after themselves, that you can let roam your base with the other sub bunnies.
§6-A lucky block.

betterquesting.name: I Can Fly Twice As High
betterquesting.desc:
Each of the three Airships has a slightly different recipe.  However, all of them will require a combination of Engines, Ignitions, Balloons, and Chassis.

§6Tip:  Dismounting in mid-air is an unfortunately common mistake.  Try to get used to the controls, and change them to suit your needs, or you may "fall" into some problems.  Keep in mind, if you Airship falls into Lava or Water, it is likely to be destroyed.

betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Dont Look Down
betterquesting.desc: You have been given dual hotbars in this pack for a reason.  Use those extra spaces to prepare for emergencies.  Keep a parachute availble in case something goes wrong.

betterquesting.name: Who Framed Amelia Aerhart?
betterquesting.desc:
Your frame can be made out of any variety of materials.  However, the material you make your frame out of determins the Maximum Velocity and Altitude that your Airship can reach.  The best frame you can currently make is most likely the Obsidian.  This will allow you to soar up to y230 and has a speed multiplier of 1.6x.  

§6As you secure more resources you can upgrade your Air Ship's frame simply by Shift+Left Clicking the new frame onto the Airship.  This will of course allow you to fly higher and faster.

betterquesting.name: Put Your Hot Air To Good Use
betterquesting.desc: You can further upgrade your airship by accessing the main panel in the ship.  Read the ugprades carefully, as each one may have an effect on your speed or fuel consumption.

betterquesting.name: Accessorize Your Ride
betterquesting.desc:
Your airship is combat ready... meaning you can fire arrows from it, drop potions, throw grenades, swing your weapon, break blocks, etc...  You are not limited.§6  HOWEVER, you will want to be very careful that you do not accidentally hit your frame or balloon while you are inside of it.  You may very well break the ship out from under you.

§bTip:  The colorizer will allow you to spice up your ship's balloon color.  You will receive a Pattern upgrade on your next quest.  These items should allow you to make an Airship that is truly one of a kind.

betterquesting.name: I Believe You Can Fly
betterquesting.desc:
Now that your airship has been crafted, the world is your Oyster.  This will make finding dungeons much easier, as you will be able to spot their entry brickways from the Air.  You can also transport mobs in your Airship... sometimes not by choice.  Use this tool to pluck them out safely, if an arrow to the head would be too harsh.

§6Tip:  These patterns will further customize your ship.  Don't worry, you can always craft a different one, if you choose to.

betterquesting.name: Luxury Even In The Worst Circumstances
betterquesting.desc:
The EnderIO inventory panel offers most of the accomodations of the bigger Storage System panels, at the cost of Nutrient Distillation.  And it works with Colossal Chests and Storage Drawers.  Just slap an Inventory Conduit onto the Chest Interface, place a Remote Awareness Upgrade into it, and then place your EnderIO Inventory Panel at the other end.  VOILA!  You can now extract, insert, and even craft items at your panel.

§6Tip:  You can either pump Nutrient distillation into the back of your panel, or disconnect the panel and place it on an EnderIO tank to fill up.  Be careful not to run out of Nutrient Distillation, or you will have to open your chest manually until you fill it up again.

betterquesting.name: Extreme Crafting At Its Finest
betterquesting.desc: The end is just the beginning.  Once you have freed the world of some of the weaker Titans, you may need some help to get further.  The Extreme Crafting system along with the Titan Rune Trade Ins will push you to the next level.  You can craft or trade for creative items, hard to get materials, and all of the tools you need to achieve greatness and fend off the remaining Titans.

betterquesting.name: Singularity?  But You Need So Many Of Them
betterquesting.desc:
The researchers back home have supplied us with a new schematic.  A machine that focusses Titan Energies into condensed matter.  In less nerdy terms, this compresses ores and minerals into Singularities, which are extremely powerful crafting materials needed to make the most extreme of items and tools.

§6Tip:  The Nuetron Collector very slowly sucks Nuetronium from the atmosphere and condenses it into pellets, which can be used in Extreme Crafting.

betterquesting.name: Bringing the Rocky Mountains To Your Door
betterquesting.desc: Just like the Igneous Extruder can create Stone, Cobblestone, and Obsidian using it's internal tanks, the Glacial Precipitator can make Snowballs, Snow, and Ice in it's internal tanks.  Another step in fully automating your processes.  This is a key function for automating the prodution of Gelid Cryotheum.

betterquesting.name: A Furnace Like No Other
betterquesting.desc:
The redstone furnace combines the flexibility of the EnderIO Smelter with the Speed of the IC2 Furnace.  It is, as usual, very easy to automate the input and output of all items.

§6Pro Tip:  Certain upgrades can change the function of a machine completely.  This Redstone Furnace reward makes the furnace ONLY process food items... but you gain additional speed and output.  Great for automating a Culinary Generator from things like Wheat/Toast.

betterquesting.name: Expansion Your Horizons
betterquesting.desc:
Thermal Expansion is about integrating processes between mods, and optimizing the performance of machinery.  The machine are all highly automatable and upgradeable.

§6Tip: Florbs are like fluid grenades.. throw them to create a source block of that liquid at the landing area.  Great for bridging over pools of lava or water.... or killing groups of huddled mobs.

betterquesting.name: Plates and More Plates
betterquesting.desc: The compactor is a fast and convenient way to automate the processing of, you guessed it, compressed items.  Most commonly, this will be plates.  These plates are also cross-compatible with the IC2 plates and can be used interchangeably.

betterquesting.name: Trashcan Smashcan
betterquesting.desc: The Nullifier is not unlike a trash can.  BUT!  It is a fancy, more expensive trash can that is sure to wow your friends.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: The sawmill will provide a whoppin 6 planks per log. This is a big step up from the manual cutting you have been doing so far to get only 2 planks per log.

betterquesting.name: Pulverier Power
betterquesting.desc: Not unlike the Sag Mill from Ender IO the pulverior breaks down ores into a fine dust powered.  This process doubles the ore ou put and can even uncover second ore type drop for more powerful armor.

betterquesting.name: Such a Sap
betterquesting.desc:
You can now harvest the inner juices of Trees to produce glue and rubber like substances that can be used interchangeably with other mods.  Simply place the Arboreal Abstractor next to a tree, and it will slowly suck the sap from within the logs.  Not all trees have sap to suck, but count on most vanilla ones being compatible.

§6Tip:  Resin from trees can be processed into Rosin, which will substitute for Rubber in most cases... allowing you to make things like Conduit Binder, Cables, and Cable Insulation.

betterquesting.name: They Can Clone Anything Nowaday
betterquesting.desc: The Phytogenic Insolator Growth Chamber is a way to automate the growth of crops without ever tilling a piece of soil.  It can duplicate and grow seeds, saplings, and/or their drops using state of the art fertilizer and RF.

betterquesting.name: Induction To Industry
betterquesting.desc: The induction smelter is the Thermal Expansion version of the Alloy Smelter.  Able to create alloys of multiple types of materials quickly, and upgradeably.

betterquesting.name: Upgrade the Machine That Upgrades Machines
betterquesting.desc: As if the speed upgrades weren't enough, you can also speed up the processing rate of the machines surrouding these Thermal Mediators.  They are like AOE Effect Time Machines.

betterquesting.name: Filler Up!
betterquesting.desc: The Fluid Transposer is your one stop shop for infusing liquids to and from items.  Turn a snowball into a cryogenically  treated Cryotheum compound... turn sand into Nether Stone... or... just fill a bucket with water.  This machine can do it all.  Make sure to check the in-GUI recipes for a list of all of the amazing things.

betterquesting.name: Water Way To Go
betterquesting.desc: If you need to automate the collection of water, but do not have an endless source available, the Aqueous Accumulator will slowly collect water from the air and store it in its internal tank.  If you place water along the sides of the accumulator it will collect water much quicker, without draining the blocks on the side.

betterquesting.name: Fractioning, I Was Never Good At Math
betterquesting.desc: The Fractioning Still seperates the small molecules of solid material from the liquid compounds pulled from natural sources.  Crude Oil, Resin, and Tar are similar components.  This allows for the materials to be processed into different, more useful items.

betterquesting.name: With Great Power, Comes Great Responsibility
betterquesting.desc: All machines in Thermal Expansion can be upgraded to multiple tiers.  This will allow them to have an increased number of upgrades.  Upgrades are also more powerful depending on the tier of machine they are in.

betterquesting.name: Let Me Upgrade Ya
betterquesting.desc: Speed Upgrades will make your machines faster and more efficient, but they will also come at the price of increased energy usage.

betterquesting.name: New Quest
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Up Up And Away
betterquesting.desc: Congratulations on your new airship.

betterquesting.name: Better With Baubles
betterquesting.desc: Baubles are trinkets that offer potion effects for as long as they are equipped.  These trinkets are equipped in your Inventory screen, next to your Character layout.  They offer a wide variety of effects from increased Mining Speed, Jump Height, or even Fire Resistance.

betterquesting.name: Shake What Your Mama Gave Ya
betterquesting.desc:
You are given a wide variety of ways to deal with the mobs you face in Craft Of The Titans.  There is no fight that should pose much of a problem, if you have exhausted all of your resources.  If you find yourself consistently dying, run through the checklist of options you have to build a better defense:

§6Natural Absorbtion - §fNatural Absorbtion is a mod the gives you a permanent shield, represented in yellow hearts above your normal health bar.  You can increase these shield hearts by crafting Natural Absorbtion books, which will be covered in the next few quests.  Unlike the Absorbtion enchant that is applied to armor, Natural Absorbtion books give you a PERMANENT shield increase.  For this reason, the cost to craft and apply the books are expensive in both materials and XP.
§6Off Hand Weaponry -§f This pack gives you the option to dual wield.  Combat is balanced around your ability to either wield two weapons, or wield a weapon with a Shield.  Shields should not be overlooked, as there are some special shields available through quests that offer traits such as Thorns XXX or Knockback XX.

betterquesting.name: Getting Started
betterquesting.desc: In Craft Of Titans you will be quickly thrust into a world of powerful enemies, exciting places to explore, and strong items to help you along the way.  This part of the guide will aid you in bypassing the usual start-of-world grind, and get you prepared to take on the Titans.

betterquesting.name: Ore and Farm Automating
betterquesting.desc:
In Craft Of The Titans you will need to balance your ability to provide power with the needs of your homeland.  In order to become stronger and face the enemies in your path, you will need the tools your homeland trades to you for care packages.  Care packages are very large orders of resources and goods which you transfer back home to your people.

Automated farms, mob grinders, ore processing, and power generation will test your ingenuity at every turn.

betterquesting.name: Generating Power
betterquesting.desc:
The End Game power options usually branch off between Large Solar Panel Arrays or Nuclear Reactor Setups.  While Nuclear Reactor setups can provide more robust power options, many players appreciate that you can start the Solar Panel energy system earlier in the game.

This section of the guide will introduce you to a few of the Power Options available at the MID-GAME level, since you will need to get your automation started, and you will not have access to the materials needed for End-Game energy options for a little while.

§3Pro Tip:  You are not expected to complete each branch of this part of the guide.  The goal is to have you select between Combustible Power (Coal, Oil, Etc..), Solar Power, or Kinetic (Windmills, Watermills, etc...).

betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Take To The Skies
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Blood Magic Mastering
betterquesting.desc:
Through the practice of mystic arts and Blood Magic, you have the ability to cast spells, summon entities to fight by your side, and even shape the world around you.  With Ars Magica 2, you can create and customize your own unique spell systems.  With Blood Magic you can harness the very Life Essence of living beings to rain destruction down upon your foes.

This section of quests will deal with some of the customized benefits of Blood Magic that you have never seen before.

betterquesting.name: Fighting Back
betterquesting.desc: As you progress through Craft Of The Titans you will inevitably gain more land, resources, machines, and valuable.  The last thing you want is a breech in your main base and a nasty creeper explosion, inferno mob fire, or general griefing.  This section of the guide will walk you through the process of setting up efficient turret defenses around your base to keep the bad guys out.

betterquesting.name: Arming Yourself
betterquesting.desc:
You will undoubtedly pick up and craft countless pieces of armor throughout the game.  There are a lot of options, made even more difficult by the fact that pieces will level up with use.  So is it worth it to swap your current piece, that has a few great level up perks... for a new piece that offers more armor value?

This portion of the guide will focus on some of the end-game armor options.  In order to take on the nastiest of Titans, including the Chaos Dragons of the The End, you will need to outfit yourself in more than just a few scraps.  Some of the most powerful armor sets in the game are:

§4Blood Magic Bound Armor - Drains your pool of life essence in exchange for damage.

§3Armor Plus Ultimate Armor - Lots of buff effects and invulnerability.

§6Draconic Evolution - Drains your RF Charge in exchange for damage.

betterquesting.name: Uncommon Titan Trades
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Into The Abyss and Above
betterquesting.desc: Abyssalcraft is a deep and dark journey through dead wastelands to battle titans that rival any you've seen in Minecraft before.  While getting your foot in the door may seem easy at first, you will quickly notice that the mobs are challenging, smart, and beefy. §6 You will be handicapping yourself if you do not take full advantage of the offensive tools of this modpack.  AoE Spells, Healing Potions, Absorbtion enchants... all of these will be coveted tools if you plan to defeat the Abyssalcraft Titans with any sanity left.

betterquesting.name: Expanding Thermally
betterquesting.desc: Thermal Expansion is a Mod that allows you to process and automate both solids and fluids in ways that you never imagined.
